  "slug": "widening-the-phrasing-space",
  "title": "If the merger line is a spectrum (forced → free) and a definition's protectability depends on how many valid phrasings the concept admits, could a canary-author deliberately widen the phrasing space by choosing an unusual metaphor or cross-field analogy for a rich concept — and would the resulting definition be more protectable, or would the very unconventionality that widens the space also make it less likely to be reproduced verbatim by adopters?",
